# grid.html

This file demonstrates the use of CSS Grid layout in HTML. It includes examples of creating responsive grids, aligning items, and customizing grid columns and rows.

## Features
- Responsive grid layout
- Customizable columns and rows
- Item alignment and spacing

## Usage
Open `grid.html` in your browser to view the grid examples. Modify the CSS and HTML to experiment with different grid configurations.

## Example
```html
<div class="grid-container">
  <div class="grid-item">1</div>
  <div class="grid-item">2</div>
  <div class="grid-item">3</div>
  <div class="grid-item">4</div>
</div>
```

```css
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: 10px;
}
.grid-item {
  background: #ccc;
  padding: 20px;
  text-align: center;
}
```
    